reviews.text: Chinese restaurant of Hunan cuisine, supposed to be hot & spicy, but not.

We are from Australia and had been craving what we call standard "chinese" food. Eg. Noodles, rice, meats, etc. Stumbled across this place by accident...was really nice, would have been 5 stars if not for the quite expensive prices. Food and service was good as was the restuarant itself...give it a go.
The food is up to standard at a reasonable price. Decor of the restaurant also provides a comfortable dinning experience.
Good food
A good authentic Wu Nan restaurant with good spicy food
